<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10717938>
    dc:description "FIGURE 4. A, Stenodynerus muelleri (Dusmet, 1917): habitus of male, habitus of female, head of male, head of female, flagellum of male, aedeagus in ventral and lateral view. B, female holotype of Stenodynerus gusenleitneri Giordani Soika, 1986: habitus in dorsal view and labels. C, Stenodynerus rufescens Giordani Soika, 1977: habitus of male, habitus of female, head of male, head of female, flagellum of male, aedeagus in ventral and lateral view." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10717938/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10717940>
    dc:description "FIGURE 5. A, Stenodynerus muelleri, gena in lateral view. B, Stenodynerus difficilis, gena in lateral view. C, Stenodynerus difficilis, pronotum in dorsal view. D, Stenodynerus fastidiosissimus, pronotum in dorsal view. E, Stenodynerus difficilis, apex of T2 in dorsal view. F, Stenodynerus laborans, apex of T2 in dorsal view. G, Stenodynerus montanus, S2 in ventral view. H, Stenodynerus fastidiosissimus, S2 in ventral view. I, Stenodynerus montanus, apex of propodeum in dorsal view. J, Stenodynerus fastidiosissimus, apex of propodeum in dorsal view. K, Stenodynerus laborans, disc of T1 in dorsal view. L, Stenodynerus difficilis, disc of T1 in dorsal view." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10717940/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

